8 Tax Commission as soon as the offenses are discovered by the Tax
9 Commission or its agents or employees. The Tax Commission shall
10 make available to the appropriate district attorney or to the
11 authorized agent of the district attorney its records and files
12 pertinent to prosecutions, and such records and files shall be fully
13 admissible as evidence for the purpose of such prosecutions.
14 SECTION 3. This act shall become effective November 1, 2025.
